        </Grid.RowDefinitions>
        <TextBlock Margin="10,10,9.6,0" TextWrapping="Wrap" VerticalAlignment="Top" Height="432" Grid.RowSpan="2"><Run FontWeight="Bold" Language="pl-pl" Text="Author: "/><Hyperlink NavigateUri="mailto:krystian@swidurski.pl"><Run FontWeight="Bold" Text="krystian@swidurski.pl"/></Hyperlink><LineBreak/><Run FontWeight="Bold" Language="pl-pl" Text="Based on: "/><Hyperlink NavigateUri="http://www.alcula.com/calculators/rpn/"><Run FontWeight="Bold" Text="http://www.alcula.com"/></Hyperlink><LineBreak/><Run FontWeight="Bold" Language="pl-pl" Text="Version: "/><Run Language="pl-pl" Text="01.11.2015"/><LineBreak/><Run FontWeight="Bold" Language="pl-pl" Text="Description: "/><Run Language="pl-pl" Text="Reverse Polish Notation (RPN) provides the quickest way to enter data in a calculator because it eliminates the need for parenthesis. It was made mainstream by HP when they implemented it in their famous programmable calculators. It is also very simple to code into a computer program. This is a simple calc written in C# and WPF. The source code is publicly available on "/><Hyperlink NavigateUri="https://github.com/TheKrystek/RPNCalculator"><Run FontWeight="Bold" Text="GitHub.com"/></Hyperlink><Run Language="pl-pl" Text=" so you can fork it."/><LineBreak/><Run Language="pl-pl"/><LineBreak/><Run FontWeight="Bold" Language="pl-pl" Text="How to use it:"/><LineBreak/><Run Language="pl-pl" Text="Unlike with a traditional calculator, you enter the parameters first, than the operator."/><LineBreak/><LineBreak/><Run Language="pl-pl" Text="For example, to calculate '20+50': type '20' -&gt; Press Enter -&gt; '50' -&gt; Press '+'"/><LineBreak/><LineBreak/><Run Language="pl-pl" Text="The "/><Run FontWeight="Bold" Language="pl-pl" Text="C"/><Run Language="pl-pl" Text=" key deletes digit from the input line."/><LineBreak/><LineBreak/><Run Language="pl-pl" Text="The "/><Run FontWeight="Bold" Language="pl-pl" Text="AC"/><Run Language="pl-pl" Text=" key clears the input line"/><LineBreak/><LineBreak/><Run Language="pl-pl" Text="Use the "/><Run FontWeight="Bold" Language="pl-pl" Text="POP"/><Run Language="pl-pl" Text=" key to remove the last value entered and shift the stack down, and the "/><Run FontWeight="Bold" Language="pl-pl" Text="SWAP "/><Run Language="pl-pl" Text="key to swap the last two elements."/><LineBreak/><LineBreak/><Run Language="pl-pl"/></TextBlock>

    </Grid>
</Window>
